Values:
0 to 9 - 0.1Hz to 1Hz in 0.1Hz increments
9 to 18 - 1Hz to 10Hz in 1Hz increments
18 to 117 - 10Hz to 1000Hz in 10Hz increments

Values:
0 - CAN baud rate
1 - CAN transmit status
2 - CAN/DAQ
3 - Function generator output
4 - Function generator frequency
5 - LCD contrast

The box ignores the data and data
length code. It simply responds
with STRING_RESPONSE_FROM_CDB
when it receives this message.

Values:
0 - Disable all
1 - Waveform0-Sawtooth0-Switches only
2 - Waveform1-Sawtooth1 only
3 - Enable all

Sets the mode for both CAN and DAQ bargraphs.
Values:
0 - Dot mode
1 - Bar mode

Periodic rate of
WAVEFORM0_SAW0_SWITCHES_FROM_CDB
equals delay multiplier * 200 nanoseconds.
Values:
Range is 0 to 65535.
